					<data id="id3">**</data>
					<data id="id4">**</data>
				</originalData>
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>Because of the convergence of interaction experiences supported by touchpads, we recommend using the <pc dataRefEnd="id2" dataRefStart="id1" id="p1"><pc dataRefEnd="id4" dataRefStart="id3" id="p2">PointerEntered</pc></pc> event to provide mouse-style UI commands in addition to the built-in support for touch input.</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
			<unit id="125" translate="yes">
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>For example, use previous and next buttons to let users flip through pages of content as well as pan through the content.</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
			<unit id="126" translate="yes">
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>The gestures and guidelines discussed in this topic can help to ensure that your app supports touchpad input seamlessly and with minimal code.</source>
